sql:
SELECT emission_factor_co2
FROM emission_factors
WHERE commodity_id = 1;

SELECT commodity_name
FROM commodities
WHERE sustainability_rating = (
    SELECT MAX(sustainability_rating)
    FROM commodities
);

SELECT commodity_name
FROM commodities
WHERE sustainability_rating = (
  SELECT MAX(sustainability_rating)
  FROM commodities
);

external_knowledge:
- The term "commodity type" refers to categories like Energy or Fossil Fuels; 
- Sustainability rating is a score on a scale (e.g., 1-10); 
- Emission factor for CO2 is measured in kg CO2/GJ; 
- Data quality score is a score indicating the quality of the data (e.g., 1-10).
